   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Cover Letter Generator\\n\",\"**NLP Project 52 of 100**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Generate tailored cover letters from a resume summary and job description using local LLM (Ollama) or Hugging Face transformers.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Use LLMs for structured text generation with templates.\\n\",\"2. Combine multiple input sources (resume + JD) into a single prompt.\\n\",\"3. Evaluate generated text quality qualitatively.\\n\",\"4. Understand prompt engineering for professional writing.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"Given a resume summary and a job description, generate a professional cover letter.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"- Job seekers spend hours writing cover letters.\\n\",\"- LLMs can draft personalized letters in seconds.\\n\",\"- This teaches prompt engineering for real business use cases.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset: Sample resumes and JDs (synthetic).\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"requests\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, requests, json\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Sample inputs\\nRESUME = \\\"\\\"\\\"Senior Python Developer with 5 years experience in machine learning, data pipelines, and cloud infrastructure.\\nSkills: Python, PyTorch, AWS, Docker, SQL, FastAPI.\\nExperience: Built ML pipelines processing 10M+ records daily. Led team of 4 engineers.\\nEducation: MS Computer Science, Stanford University.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nJD = \\\"\\\"\\\"We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer to join our AI team.\\nResponsibilities: Design and deploy ML models, build data pipelines, collaborate with product teams.\\nRequirements: 3+ years Python, experience with PyTorch or TensorFlow, AWS experience preferred.\\nNice to have: Experience with LLMs, RAG systems, and MLOps.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nprint('Resume:', RESUME[:100])\\nprint('JD:', JD[:100])\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Cover Letter Generation via Ollama (Local LLM)\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We'll try to use a local Ollama model first. If unavailable, we fall back to a template-based approach.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"OLLAMA_URL = 'http://localhost:11434/api/generate'\\n\\ndef generate_with_ollama(resume, jd, model='qwen3:1.7b'):\\n    prompt = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Write a professional cover letter for this job application.\\n\\nResume Summary:\\n{resume}\\n\\nJob Description:\\n{jd}\\n\\nWrite a 3-paragraph cover letter that:\\n1. Opens with enthusiasm for the specific role\\n2. Highlights relevant experience matching the JD requirements\\n3. Closes with a call to action\\n\\nKeep it professional, concise, and under 250 words. /no_think\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    try:\\n        resp = requests.post(OLLAMA_URL, json={'model': model, 'prompt': prompt, 'stream': False}, timeout=120)\\n        return resp.json().get('response', 'Generation failed.')\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        return f'Ollama unavailable: {e}'\\n\\nresult = generate_with_ollama(RESUME, JD)\\nprint('=== Generated Cover Letter ===')\\nprint(result)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Fallback: Template-Based Generation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re\\n\\ndef template_cover_letter(resume, jd):\\n    # Extract key skills from JD\\n    jd_skills = set(re.findall(r'\\\\b(?:Python|PyTorch|TensorFlow|AWS|Docker|SQL|MLOps|LLMs|RAG)\\\\b', jd, re.IGNORECASE))\\n    resume_skills = set(re.findall(r'\\\\b(?:Python|PyTorch|TensorFlow|AWS|Docker|SQL|MLOps|LLMs|RAG|FastAPI)\\\\b', resume, re.IGNORECASE))\\n    matching = jd_skills & resume_skills\\n    \\n    letter = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Dear Hiring Manager,\\n\\nI am excited to apply for the Machine Learning Engineer position. With my background in {', '.join(list(matching)[:3]) if matching else 'relevant technologies'}, I am confident I can contribute meaningfully to your AI team.\\n\\nIn my current role, I have built production ML pipelines and collaborated with cross-functional teams. My experience with {', '.join(list(resume_skills)[:4])} directly aligns with your requirements. I am particularly drawn to the opportunity to work on cutting-edge AI systems.\\n\\nI would welcome the chance to discuss how my experience can benefit your team. Thank you for considering my application.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n[Your Name]\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return letter\\n\\ntemplate_result = template_cover_letter(RESUME, JD)\\nprint('=== Template-Based Cover Letter ===')\\nprint(template_result)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Comparison\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f'LLM-generated length: {len(result.split())} words')\\nprint(f'Template-based length: {len(template_result.split())} words')\\nprint(f'\\\\nSkill matching: JD requires specific skills, cover letter should mention them.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **LLMs produce more natural, varied cover letters** than templates.\\n\",\"- **Template-based is reliable** but generic.\\n\",\"- **Prompt engineering matters** — specific instructions improve output quality.\\n\",\"- **For production, combine LLM generation with skill-matching validation.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
